                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/215: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-18T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 18, 1929—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[729.] Legation’s 727, August 18, noon. Following from the American Consul at
                    Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 17, noon. Have learned confidentially that a telegram has been
                            received by the Government this morning that Soviet troops started
                            bombarding Manchuria Station 3 o’clock this morning. Matter being
                            investigated; will report any further particulars obtained.”</p>
                        <p>“August 17, 10 p.m. Referring to my despatch of August 17, noon. Official
                            telegram from Tsitsihar received by Government this afternoon states
                            that 10,000 Soviet troops with 30 field pieces and machine guns crossed
                            border and attacked between Manchuli and Chalainor. Fifty Chinese
                            soldiers killed. Semiofficial source states Mukden sending 40,000 troops
                            north, half to western and half to eastern front.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
